This repository will hold some code used in a ruleby screen cast. 
-----------------------------------------------------------------

The first screencast is planned to be in french, but code and comments will be in english for broader use.

This readme will be updated as soon as content is added.

To know more about ruleby : https://github.com/Codalytics/ruleby

Sources files have been commented in markdown in order to be processed with docco.

# How to start ? 
The first thing to understand after you have read content of ruleby Wiki is how to write LHS (Left Hand Side) of rules.
the file LHS_examples.markdown demonstrate differents use. Please tell me if anything you see could be done better or even 
if there is a good alternative I should present.